Extract specific components from video files such as audio tracks, subtitles, single frames, or the raw video without audio/subs.

# Description
#-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Extract **all audio tracks** as `.mp3`
- Extract **all or selected subtitles** in the format of your choice (`srt`, `ass`, `vtt`)
- Extract a **single frame** at a specific timestamp or at the middle of the video
- Create a **video-only version** without audio or subtitles

# Arguments (Flags)
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- `--files`               Input file(s) or patterns (e.g. `clip%.mp4`)
- `--audio`               Extract all audio streams (e.g. `file_audio0.mp3`, `file_audio1.mp3`)
- `--subtitle NAME`       Extract subtitle by name (or all, if unspecified)
- `--format srt|ass|vtt`  Subtitle export format (default: `srt`)
- `--frame TIME`          Extract frame at `TIME` (e.g. `00:02:30`) â€“ default is middle of video
- `--video`               Remove all audio/subs, output video only

# Interactive fallback
#--------------------------------
If none of the above flags are set, the user will be prompted to choose one or more of the extract types interactively.

# Examples
#-----------------------------------------------------------------
video extract --files movie.mp4 --audio
video extract --subtitle German --format ass
video extract --frame 90
video extract --video
video extract clip%.mp4         # Interactive mode (choose a/s/f/v)

#---
Note: Extracted files will be named based on the input (e.g. `video_audio0.mp3`, `video_sub0.srt`, `video_frame.png`, `video_video.mp4`).

